        "client_msg_id": "53e04784-e848-40b7-af18-ccefd36315a0",
        "text": "I only became aware of the manifesto when Wesley posted their own criticism, which I very much agreed with: <https:\/\/notebook.wesleyac.com\/resonant-computing\/|https:\/\/notebook.wesleyac.com\/resonant-computing\/>\n\nI was a bit surprised there were a lot of people I recognize and respect as authors\/signatures. Directionally it seems _fine_, but it just doesn't... add much concrete value? Which I feel is what Wesley was pointing out.\n\n&gt; It feels a bit rude sometimes to do a close reading of a text that is not very rigorously thought through, but I hope that the authors are able to appreciate that doing this sort of reading is taking their ideas seriously, and I hope that they are willing to take their own ideas seriously enough to consider them.",
